WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'InterBall' is a Workbench game in which you burst balls by
clicking on them. Points are made when at least 3 balls of the
same colour, located next to each other, burst. As the balls are
of 4 different sizes, you have to click on the smaller balls to
increase their size before they will burst.

  As balls burst, balls or other objects that are located over
them will fall in the emptied spaces and so on. A "gauge", located
at the right of the game board, indicates how many balls are
surrounded by 2 (or more) balls of the same colour. When the gauge
is empty (no coloured rectangles appear there), the game is over.

  Have fun!

